The paper discusses extensions to Answer Set Programming (ASP), which is a subfield of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper specifically focuses on the semantics and compilation of programs with generalized atoms, which are a type of logical construct used in ASP. This topic falls under the subfields of Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO), Programming Languages (cs.PL), and Databases (cs.DB). Additionally, the paper discusses complexity results, which could also place it in the subfield of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS).
